data.title: Vandenberg AFB History
data.meta_description: Vandenberg AFB History - Free download as PDF File (.pdf) or read online for free. This document provides historical documentation of Space Launch Complex 10 (SLC-10) at Vandenberg Air Force Base in California. It summarizes that SLC-10 was built in 1958-1959 by Douglas Aircraft Company and was used for Thor rocket launches during the Cold War era, including for training the Royal Air Force and for anti-satellite testing. SLC-10 launched several Defense Meteorological Satellite Program satellites and has been recognized as a National Historic Landmark for its role in the US space program in the 1950s. The document includes architectural descriptions and photographs of the facilities at SLC-10.
